---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="How We Find Trends" description="Our weekly workflow for spotting US trending products and high-commission opportunities.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>How we find trends (your weekly job)</h1>
    <p>You don't need to guess US demand. Use data + speed. Publish within 48 hours of spotting a spike.</p>

    <h2>Step 1 — Daily radar (30 min)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://trends.google.com/trends/" rel="nofollow">Google Trends</a> → United States → last 7 days</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/movers-and-shakers" rel="nofollow">Amazon Movers & Shakers</a></li>
      <li>Reddit: r/AmazonFinds, r/BuyItForLife, r/ArtificialInteligence (hot posts)</li>
      <li>X/Twitter search: "tiktok made me buy", "viral amazon"</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Step 2 — Filter (pick 1–3 per week)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Search volume <strong>rising</strong>, not just one-day noise</li>
      <li>You can monetize: Amazon link OR SaaS affiliate (AI tools pay more)</li>
      <li>You can publish a page in <strong>under 4 hours</strong></li>
      <li>Prefer buyer intent: "best", "worth it", "vs", "alternatives"</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Step 3 — Publish fast</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Add entry to <code>src/data/trends.json</code></li>
      <li>Run <code>npm run build</code> and deploy</li>
      <li>Optional: add a micro-tool in <code>src/data/tools.json</code></li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Step 4 — Promote (same day)</h2>
    <p>Hot trends die in SEO time. Post links on Reddit/X the same day — don't wait for Google.</p>

    <h2>Commission priority (high → low)</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>AI / SaaS affiliates</strong> — 20–40% recurring</li>
      <li><strong>Amazon trending gadgets</strong> — volume, 3–8%</li>
      <li><strong>Game launch accessories</strong> — 60-day spike windows</li>
      <li><strong>AdSense</strong> — baseline after traffic lands</li>
    </ol>
  </article>
</Layout>
